In order to quantify the impact of this bottleneck, we also consider an unconstrained model that replace the questionnaire model in the previous methods by only a BERT encoder.
This gives a loose upper bound on the classifier-constrained methods's performance since this approach has access to the raw BERT embeddings and thus can utilize more signals (even spurious ones) than those captured by the questionnaire model.